The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) says it will meet with the Nigerian National Petroleum Company (NNPC) Limited to address the fuel crisis across the country ahead of the general elections in February and March. Nigeria has since been grappling with prolonged petrol scarcity, which has been attributed to inadequate supply of the product by the NNPCL, the sole importer of Premium Motor Spirit. READ ALSO: 2023 Election: INEC Extends Deadline For PVC Collection The National Commissioner and Chairman, Information and Voter Education Committee, INEC, Festus Okoye, told Punch that the commission was prepared to resolve issues regarding logistics ahead of the polls. Okoye said, “The issue relating to logistics, we are going to deal with it. We are going to hold a high-level meeting with the NNPCL to resolve whatever issues or challenges we have. “We are going to solve the issues based on our own processes and procedures. We have things under control.”  